author: Dailymail.Com Reporter
title: Dozens protest Army Corps of Engineers over pipeline | Daily Mail Online
text: Dozens protest outside the Army Corps of Engineers offices in Los Angeles after the agency said it will clear the way for completion of the $3.8billion North Dakota pipeline Dozens protested outside Army Corps of Engineers office in Los Angeles Protest came after agency cleared way for completion of Dakota pipeline Energy Transfer Partners (ETP) received final permission from Army Wednesday The Standing Rock Sioux tribe fears a leak would pollute its drinking water But ETP says the pipeline is safe and operations could begin as early as June Published: 06:50 GMT, 9 February 2017 | Updated: 14:46 GMT, 9 February 2017 181 shares
